          <h2 class="featurette-heading">Symbol of Freedom. <span class="text-muted">The fruit of struggle.</span></h2>
          <p class="lead">Cuba's flag symbolizes the country and its freedom and has done so since 1902, after their independence. The blue stripes represent Cuba's three states of 1902. The white stripes represent the durability of the independist ideal. A red triangle displays blood from the struggle, as well as "equality, fraternity, and freedom". Finally, the star represents absolute freedom among peoples. </p>
        </div>
